Set the death signal on Envoy and CoreDNS child processes. This causes
the kernel to send SIGKILL to these processes if the kuma-dp process exits
unexpectedly (e.g. panics or is killed). This improves the resiliency of
the dataplane since restarting would not encounter stale child processes.

When the flag is set, kumactl should not try to create a config
file.

config file, and can be run on read-only filesystems, as it
happens to be true for example on GKE

timed, asynchronous test functions is deprecated and doesn't work
correctly. Replacing all these usages with a local test helper removes
the Ginkgo deprecation warnings and (at least for my environment) makes
the tests reliably pass.

[{"sha":"c78f78dc015b8b75fd7ba5e0186899f755eeb8ef","author":{"name":"T.J. Alumbaugh","email":"62ef278d14cf507ef535afc13ea89a9f9f2de11e@google.com"},"message":"Permit setting accumulation type for fp16 inference.

Adds an experimental "supported accumulation type" to the TargetSpec.
This allows model authors to specify, for example, that a float16 quantized
model can actually use float16 accumulators in quantized operations. This can
facilitate increased performance for delegates that can take advantage of such
information. A future work will provide conversion assistance to help ensure that
a model can still provide good accuracy with such a setting.

[{"sha":"53931158504a88468ff35bfd492b529876a04697","author":{"name":"Antonio Sanchez","email":"d7c4f796bb044488ce75bcb289e0b6840bbb0be8@google.com"},"message":"Add explicit casts to outputs of std::math ops for f16/bf16.

When calling `std::math` functions, half-float and bfloat16 will
be implicitly converted to float to call the float versions, returning
float. The result, however, will not be implicitly cast back to the
original type since doing so results in a loss of precision.  We
need to correct this by adding explicit casts.
